What is if?
It is used to check a condition and when condition is true then if block will execute other wise if block will not execute.
Syntax:
if(condition){
   // code
}

Example: -
int age = 20;

if(age >= 18){
    System.out.println("Eligible to vote");
}

1.2	What is if else?
It is used to check a condition and if block will execute when a condition will be true otherwise else will execute.
Syntax: -
if(condition){
   // true block
} else {
   // false block
}

Example: -
int num = 5;

if(num % 2 == 0){
    System.out.println("Even");
} else {
    System.out.println("Odd");
}

